<DOC><DOCNO> AP891204-0060 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-04-89 0946EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Korea-Crash     12-04 0170</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Korea-Crash,0175</SECOND><HEAD>U.S. Army Helicopter Crashes; All Aboard Safe</HEAD><DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A U.S. Army helicopter carrying 16soldiers and a crew of three crashed into a remote mountainsidesouth of Seoul today, but only minor injuries were reported,officials said.   The CH-47D Chinook transport helicopter was on a trainingmission when it crashed near Osan City, 40 miles south of Seoul, atabout 10:30 a.m., said Air Force Sgt. Wilt Baker of the 8th U.S.Army public affairs office.   The injured were treated at nearby hospitals, he said. Theirnames were withheld.   The helicopter was assigned to B Company, 2nd Battalion, 501stAviation Regiment stationed at Camp Humphreys south of Seoul.American military officials said they were investigating the causeof the crash.   The Army grounded most of its CH-47D Chinook helicopters inOctober because of a problem with transmission oil cooling fans.The fleet was grounded in August as a precaution while previous fanfailures were studied.   The helicopters were made by Boeing Helicopter Co.</TEXT></DOC>